0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=219822\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:644:\"<p>Do you want to move your WordPress site from a local server to a live site? Deploying your WordPress site on a local server is one of the best ways to speed up the development process. It helps you ensure that your WordPress site works perfectly, even before bringing in traffic. The easiest way to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-transfer-wordpress-from-local-server-to-a-live-site-step-by-step/\">How to Transfer WordPress from Local Server to a Live Site (Step by Step)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27602:\"<p>Do you want to move your WordPress site from a local server to a live site? Deploying your WordPress site on a local server is one of the best ways to speed up the development process. It helps you ensure that your WordPress site works perfectly, even before bringing in traffic.</p>\n<p>The easiest way to transfer your WordPress site from a local server to a live site is by using a WordPress plugin like <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/backupbuddy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">BackupBuddy</a> or <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/duplicator-pro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Duplicator</a>.</p>\n<p>If you’d rather move your WordPress site without using any plugins from a local server to a live site, just follow the step-by-step guide below.</p>\n<p>But if you still want to do it the easier way, don&#8217;t worry. We&#8217;ll show you how to transfer WordPress from a local server to a live site using the Duplicator plugin at the end of this article as well. </p>\n<h3>Moving WordPress from a Local Server to a Live Site- Prerequisites</h3>\n<p>Before you begin, we’re assuming that you have a WordPress site running on your local server and you have full access to it.</p>\n<p>You’ll also need to purchase a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/difference-between-domain-name-and-web-hosting-revealed/\">domain name and web hosting</a>.</p>\n<p>If you don’t own a domain and web hosting, then we recommend you to get it first before you begin. If you’re just starting out, the combined cost of domain and hosting can seem like quite a lot.</p>\n<p>That’s why we’ve worked out a deal with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluehost</a> to offer our users a free domain name, free SSL, and over 60% off on WordPress hosting.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Click here to Claim this Exclusive Bluehost Offer &raquo;</a></p>\n<p>Finally, you’ll also need to have an FTP program installed on your computer and know <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/how-to-use-ftp-to-upload-files-to-wordpress-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\">how to use it</a>, so you can upload your content and files to the live site.</p>\n<p>Once you’re ready, you can go ahead with migration.</p>\n<h3>Table of Contents &#8211; Migrating WordPress From a Local Server to a Live Site</h3>\n<p>I. Transferring a Site Without a Plugin</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#export-database\">Export Your Database From a Local Server</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#import-wordpress-files\">Import WordPress Files to a Live Site</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#create-mysql-database\">Create a MySQL Database on Live Site</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#import-wordpress-database\">Import WordPress Database to Production Site</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#change-website-url\">Change the Website URL</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#configure-wordpress\">Configure WordPress in Your Web Hosting</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fix-images\">Fix Images and Broken Links</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>II. Transferring a Website With a Plugin (Duplicator)</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#setup-duplicator\">Install and Setup Duplicator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#create-database\">Create a Database for Your Live Site</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#import-files\">Import Files from Your Local Server</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#run-script\">Run the Migration Script</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"export-database\">Step 1: Export Your Database from Your Local Server</h3>\n<p>The first thing you need to do is export your local WordPress database. To do that, we’ll be using phpMyAdmin. If you’re not familiar with phpMyAdmin and need assistance with this step, then check out <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/beginners-guide-to-wordpress-database-management-with-phpmyadmin/\">WordPress database management using phpMyAdmin</a>.</p>\n<p>In your browser, simply go to http://localhost/phpmyadmin/ and click on your WordPress database. Next, click on the <strong>Export</strong> button from the top menu bar.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-database-from-local-server.png\" alt=\"export database from local server\" width=\"550\" height=\"99\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219833\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-database-from-local-server.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-database-from-local-server-300x54.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>You’ll now be asked to choose from <strong>Quick</strong> or <strong>Custom</strong> options. Choosing the Custom option provides you with a lot of different options to export your database. For a quick export, let’s choose <strong>Quick</strong>, and then hit <strong>Go</strong>. This will download your database.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-mysql-database.png\" alt=\"export mysql database\" width=\"505\" height=\"325\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219834\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-mysql-database.png 505w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-mysql-database-300x193.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"import-wordpress-files\">Step 2: Upload Your WordPress Files to the Live Site</h3>\n<p>After exporting the database, the next step is to move all your site files to your live site.</p>\n<p>In this step, you need to use your FTP client to upload your files. First, connect your FTP client to your web hosting account.</p>\n<p>Once it’s connected, choose the correct directory in your hosting account where you want to upload the files. For example, if you plan to host the site on example.com, then you’d want to upload all files in your public_html directory.</p>\n<p>Now, select all your local WordPress files and upload them to your live server.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/upload-wordpress-files.png\" alt=\"upload wordpress files\" width=\"520\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219827\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/upload-wordpress-files.png 520w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/upload-wordpress-files-300x202.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"create-mysql-database\">Step 3: Create a MySQL Database on Your Live Site</h3>\n<p>While your FTP client is uploading your WordPress files, you can start importing your database to the live server. Most <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/managed-wordpress-hosting-reviews/\" title=\"The Best Managed WordPress Hosting Companies\">WordPress hosting</a> providers offer a cPanel to manage your hosting account. In this step, we’ll show you how to create a database by logging into your cPanel.</p>\n<p>After you&#8217;ve logged into your cPanel, click the <strong>MySQL Databases</strong> icon which is usually found in the Databases section.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/my-sql-databases.png\" alt=\"mysql databases\" width=\"467\" height=\"180\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219836\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/my-sql-databases.png 467w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/my-sql-databases-300x116.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 467px) 100vw, 467px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen that appears, specify the name for your database in the <strong>New Database</strong> field and then click <strong>Create Database</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/create-a-new-database.png\" alt=\"create a new database\" width=\"520\" height=\"127\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219831\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/create-a-new-database.png 520w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/create-a-new-database-300x73.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px\" /></p>\n<p>Now that a new database was created, scroll down to the MySQL Users section and create or add an existing user to the database.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/create-mysql-database-user.png\" alt=\"create mysql database user\" width=\"550\" height=\"574\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219832\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/create-mysql-database-user.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/create-mysql-database-user-287x300.png 287w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>After adding the user, you’ll be prompted to set MySQL privileges for that user. Simply grant all privileges to the user, and then hit the <strong>Make Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/all-priveleges.png\" alt=\"all privileges\" width=\"523\" height=\"361\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219828\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/all-priveleges.png 523w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/all-priveleges-300x207.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 523px) 100vw, 523px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"import-wordpress-database\">Step 4: Import WordPress Database on Your Live Site</h3>\n<p>Next, you’ll have to import your WordPress database to your production site. In your cPanel, scroll down to the Databases section and click on <strong>phpMyAdmin</strong>. This will direct you to the phpMyAdmin section. Make sure to select the database you created in the previous step, which has no tables created.</p>\n<p>Click the Import tab from within the top menu. Select the file you want to import by clicking <strong>Choose File</strong>. Make sure to choose the correct file that you’ve downloaded in the first step from your local server.</p>\n<p>After selecting the file, click the <strong>Go</strong> button to import your WordPress database.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-database.png\" alt=\"import database\" width=\"545\" height=\"305\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219835\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-database.png 545w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-database-300x168.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 545px) 100vw, 545px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"change-website-url\">Step 5: Change the Site URL</h3>\n<p>The next thing you need to do is change the site URL in your database so that it connects with your live WordPress site.</p>\n<p>In phpMyAdmin, look for the wp_options table in your database that you’ve just imported in the last step. In case you <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-change-the-wordpress-database-prefix-to-improve-security/\" target=\"_blank\">changed your database prefix</a>, then look for {prefix}_options instead of wp_options.</p>\n<p>Select the <strong>Browse</strong> button that you can find next to wp_options. Alternatively, you can browse the wp_options table by clicking on it in the sidebar as shown in the screenshot below.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/browse-wp-options.jpg\" alt=\"browse wp_options\" width=\"550\" height=\"287\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219829\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/browse-wp-options.jpg 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/browse-wp-options-300x157.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>In the <strong>option_name</strong> column, look for siteurl. To edit the site URL, click the <strong>Edit</strong> icon as shown in the screenshot.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/siteurl.png\" alt=\"edit siteurl\" width=\"550\" height=\"123\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219826\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/siteurl.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/siteurl-300x67.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>Clicking on the Edit icon will open an edit field window. Make sure to replace the URL shown in the option_value box with your domain name.</p>\n<p>Hit the <strong>Go</strong> button to save the field.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/change-site-url.png\" alt=\"change-site-url\" width=\"656\" height=\"546\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219830\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/change-site-url.png 656w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/change-site-url-300x250.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 656px) 100vw, 656px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to replicate this step for the option name: home. The wp_options page can be a few pages long, so simply find the home tab. Usually, it is on the second page, which you can navigate to by clicking on the pagination arrows in phpMyAdmin.</p>\n<p>When you’re updating the home url, make sure that it’s same as your siteurl.</p>\n<h3 id=\"configure-wordpress\">Step 6: Configure WordPress in Your Web Hosting</h3>\n<p>Next, it’s time to configure WordPress in the production environment.</p>\n<p>If you try to access your site now, you may find a message like this: <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-fix-the-error-establishing-a-database-connection-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Error Establishing Database Connection</a>. By configuring WordPress, our goal is to fix this error and set up the live site.</p>\n<p>Go back to your FTP client and connect it to your website and then edit your wp-config.php file. In this step, you’ll have to add the same database name, user, and password to your wp-config.php as you created in Step 3. Then, save the wp-config.php file and upload it back to your web host.</p>\n<p>Visit your website, and it should be live now.</p>\n<p>Next, you need to login to your WordPress dashboard and navigate to <strong>Settings &raquo; General</strong>. Without making any modifications, scroll to the bottom and click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button. This will ensure that the site URL is corrected anywhere else that it needs to be.</p>\n<p>Next, head over to <strong>Settings &raquo; Permalink</strong> and click <strong>Save Changes</strong> to ensure that all your post links are working fine.</p>\n<h3 id=\"fix-images\">Step 7: Fix Images and Broken Links by Updating Paths</h3>\n<p>One of the common issues you might find while <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/move-wordpress-to-new-domain-name/\" title=\"How to Properly Move WordPress to a New Domain Name\">migrating your WordPress site from one domain to another</a>, or from a local server to a live site, is that you&#8217;ll discover broken links and missing images throughout the site after migration. To fix this, you can either use an SQL query or the <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-update-urls-when-moving-your-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\">Velvet Blues WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>For those who want to do it via SQL, here is a simple SQL query that should solve this problem:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\r\nUPDATE wp_posts SET post_content = REPLACE(post_content, \'localhost/test/\', \'www.yourlivesite.com/\');\r\n</pre>\n<p>Simply go to phpMyAdmin, click on your database, and then click on SQL from the top menu. Write this query, but make sure to modify the URL of your local site and live site.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/run-sql.jpg\" alt=\"run sql\" width=\"550\" height=\"308\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-219825\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/run-sql.jpg 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/run-sql-300x168.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s it! Your live site should be up and running now.</p>\n<h2>Transferring WordPress from Local Server to Live Site with a Plugin</h2>\n<p>If you want to move WordPress from a local server to a live site easily, this is the best method for beginners. With a migration plugin, you can transfer WordPress from your local server to a live site with just a few clicks.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s begin. </p>\n<h3 id=\"setup-duplicator\">Step 1: Install and Setup the Duplicator Plugin</h3>\n<p>First, you need to choose a migration plugin, we recommend choosing <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/duplicator-pro/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Duplicator</a>. </p>\n<p>Next, install and activate the plugin on your local site. If you&#8217;re not sure how to install and activate a WordPress plugin, check out our detailed guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-wordpress-plugin/\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>After the Duplicator plugin is installed and activated, click on <strong>Duplicator</strong> in your WordPress dashboard, click on <strong>Packages</strong>, and then click on the <strong>Create New</strong> button.  </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-create-new.jpg\" alt=\"duplicator-create-new-package\" width=\"740\" height=\"334\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233525\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-create-new.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-create-new-300x135.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen, simply click the <strong>Next</strong> button. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-create-new-package.jpg\" alt=\"create-new-package-next\" width=\"740\" height=\"272\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233526\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-create-new-package.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-create-new-package-300x110.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Duplicator will then scan everything to make sure it&#8217;s all in good order. If all of the items in the system scan come back marked as &#8216;Good&#8217;, then click on the <strong>Build</strong> button. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-scan-complete.jpg\" alt=\"duplicator-scan-complete\" width=\"705\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233641\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-scan-complete.jpg 705w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-scan-complete-300x213.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 705px) 100vw, 705px\" /></p>\n<p>This process of &#8220;building&#8221; may take a few minutes. Because what the plugin is doing is making a complete copy of your WordPress site. This includes all the core WordPress files as well as your themes, plugins, images, uploads, and a backup of your WordPress database. So, the time it takes depends on the size of your website. Make sure to leave this tab open until the process is complete. </p>\n<p>Once the process is complete, you can click on the <strong>One-Click Download</strong> button to download both the Installer and Archive package files to your computer. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/downloadpackage-1.png\" alt=\"download-package\" width=\"550\" height=\"284\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233699\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/downloadpackage-1.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/downloadpackage-1-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"create-database\">Step 2: Create a Database for your Live Site</h3>\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve downloaded the Archive file of your site and the Installer file, which will automate the migration by unpacking the archive file, you need to create a MySQL database for your live website. </p>\n<p>To create a database, go to your hosting account&#8217;s cPanel dashboard. Once there, scroll down to the Databases section and click on the <strong>MySQL Databases</strong> icon. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/my-sql-databases.jpg\" alt=\"my-sql-databases\" width=\"639\" height=\"132\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233644\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/my-sql-databases.jpg 639w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/my-sql-databases-300x62.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, 639px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll see a field called &#8216;Create New Database&#8217;. Simply type in a name for your database and click on the <strong>Create Database</strong> button. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-new-database-1.jpg\" alt=\"create-new-database\" width=\"740\" height=\"123\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233683\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-new-database-1.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-new-database-1-300x50.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you click that button, cPanel will create a new database for you. </p>\n<p>The next step is to scroll down the page to the &#8216;MySQL Users&#8217; section. Add a new user by creating a username and password. Then, click on the <strong>Create a User</strong> button. Be sure to remember your username and password because you&#8217;ll need them again later. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-new-user.jpg\" alt=\"add-new-user\" width=\"662\" height=\"254\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233684\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-new-user.jpg 662w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-new-user-300x115.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 662px) 100vw, 662px\" /></p>\n<p>After creating the new user, you&#8217;ll need to give that new user permission to work on the database. To do that, scroll down to the &#8216;Add a User to Database&#8217; section. Select the new user you just created from the dropdown menu in the &#8216;User&#8217; field. Then, select the database you created from the dropdown in the &#8216;Database&#8217; field. Finally, click the <strong>Add</strong> button. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-user-to-database.jpg\" alt=\"add-user-to-database\" width=\"550\" height=\"130\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233686\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-user-to-database.jpg 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-user-to-database-300x71.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>Now your database is ready to be used with your WordPress site. </p>\n<h3 id=\"import-files\">Step 3: Upload Files from Local Server to Live Site</h3>\n<p>The next step is to upload the archive and installer files from your local site to your hosting account. </p>\n<p>You can connect to your live site using an FTP client. After you&#8217;ve connected to your live site, it&#8217;s important to make sure the root directory of your website is empty. The root directory is typically the /home/public_html/ folder.</p>\n<p>For instance, if WordPress is automatically installed there like many <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/\">website hosting companies</a> do when you sign up, you need to delete those files. </p>\n<p>When the root directory is completely empty, you can upload the archive and installer files from Duplicator.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/filesinrootdir.png\" alt=\"upload-files-root-directory\" width=\"550\" height=\"296\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233700\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/filesinrootdir.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/filesinrootdir-300x161.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /> </p>\n<h3 id=\"run-script\">Step 4: Run the Migration Script</h3>\n<p>Next, visit the following URL in your browser: http://mywebsite.com/installer.php</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to replace &#8220;my website&#8221; with the actual domain name. </p>\n<p>Entering this URL in your browser will launch the Duplicator migration wizard. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup1.png\" alt=\"duplicator-migration-wizard\" width=\"550\" height=\"332\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233702\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup1.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup1-300x181.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>A validation test will be performed, once you get the green pass, accept the terms &#038; conditions by checking the box and hit the <strong>Next</strong> button. </p>\n<p>On the next screen you&#8217;ll enter your WordPress database information which includes the username and password you created earlier. </p>\n<p>Hint: It will also ask you for your host which is likely &#8220;localhost&#8221;. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-install-database.jpg\" alt=\"duplicator-install-database\" width=\"740\" height=\"414\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233707\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-install-database.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/duplicator-install-database-300x168.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Click <strong>Next</strong> to continue. </p>\n<p>The Duplicator plugin will now import your WordPress database from the archive to your new database. </p>\n<p>Next, the update data screen appears. The plugin automatically detects the URL of your new site and it&#8217;s path though, so you don&#8217;t actually have to update anything here. Just click <strong>Next</strong> to continue.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup3.png\" alt=\"update-duplicator\" width=\"550\" height=\"244\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233705\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup3.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup3-300x133.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>After the migration process is complete, you&#8217;ll see a success screen like the one below. From here you can go to the WordPress admin area of your live site by clicking the <strong>Admin Login</strong> button. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup4.png\" alt=\"duplicator-admin-login\" width=\"550\" height=\"229\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233706\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup4.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dup4-300x125.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it, your work is done. Once you login to your live site, Duplicator will clean up the installation files for you. </p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you successfully move your WordPress site from a local server to a live site. Now, go back to your live site and figure out if everything is working as expected.</p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can use <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/backupbuddy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">BackupBuddy</a> instead to migrate WordPress from a local server to a live site.</p>\n<p>If you enjoyed this article, you might also want to check out the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-backup-plugins-compared/\">best backup plugins for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-transfer-wordpress-from-local-server-to-a-live-site-step-by-step/\">How to Transfer WordPress from Local Server to a Live Site (Step by Step)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-transfer-wordpress-from-local-server-to-a-live-site-step-by-step/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"Divi Theme &amp; Builder Review (2019): Is It Worth the Price?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-themes/divi-theme-review/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:67:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-themes/divi-theme-review/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 31 May 2019 15:40:45 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"http://www.isitwp.com/?post_type=isitwp_theme&p=155\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:454:\"<p>Divi is one of the most popular multi-purpose WordPress themes in the market. It is created by Elegant Themes, one of the leading WordPress theme shops in the world.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-themes/divi-theme-review/\">Divi Theme &#038; Builder Review (2019): Is It Worth the Price?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Allison Hott\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15996:\"<p>Divi is one of the most popular WordPress themes on the market. Created by Elegant Themes, one of the leading WordPress theme shops in the world, Divi is a beautiful multi-purpose WordPress theme. In this Divi theme review, we&#8217;ll take a deeper look at its feature and check out what all the fuss is about.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-main.jpg\" alt=\"divi-theme\" width=\"740\" height=\"392\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232065\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-main.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-main-300x159.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<h2>About Divi Theme</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> is created by Elegant Themes, which is one of the leading WordPress theme companies in the world. </p>\n<p>Divi is included in Elegant Themes theme club membership which gives you access to 2 themes (Divi and Extra) and 2 plugins (Bloom and Monarch) for the price of a single theme. You&#8217;ll also get hundreds of Divi website packs that let you quickly launch a site of any type without having to build from the ground up. </p>\n<p>For 10 years, the company has been providing premium WordPress support for their products that power a large number of websites.</p>\n<p>Although Elegant Themes is headquartered in San Francisco, they are a distributed workforce with over 70 employees all over the world.</p>\n<h2>Divi Theme Review: Powerful Theme Packaged With 100+ Site Packs</h2>\n<p>As a premium theme and plugin developer, Elegant Themes knows what WordPress users want from a powerful theme. They want flexibility and features packed into one nice bundle.</p>\n<blockquote><p>Divi was everything I wished for! Easy to use modules, drag-and-drop design, predefined layouts, the Customize panel and the Custom CSS box all make for an exceptionally fast, efficient way to create clean, modern sites that clients are looking for.</p>\n<footer>-Kathy Kroll Romana</footer>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at some of the main features of Divi Theme.</p>\n<h3>Build any Kind of Website With the Divi Builder</h3>\n<p>When you purchase an Elegant Themes membership, you&#8217;ll find 2 different flavors of <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> in your dashboard: Divi Theme and Divi Builder (plugin).</p>\n<p>All themes released by Elegant Themes, including the Divi Theme are shipped with the drag and drop Divi Builder that lets you easily build and customize your website.</p>\n<p>If you want a highly customizable WordPress theme, then you can use Divi Theme. Alternatively, if you want to use a different theme but also need a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-page-builders-compared/\" title=\"7 Best Drag and Drop WordPress Page Builders Compared\">drag and drop page builder plugin</a>, then you can use the Divi builder.</p>\n<p>With Divi Builder’s default editor, you can easily drag and drop rows, columns, elements, and modules to create beautiful layouts on your own. This allows you to create a fully-customized site in no time at all, without touching a line of code.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-builder-interface.jpg\" alt=\"divi-builder-interface\" width=\"687\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232069\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-builder-interface.jpg 687w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-builder-interface-300x218.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 687px) 100vw, 687px\" /> </p>\n<p>Each module in your layout can be removed or duplicated with the click of a button. The modules are also clearly labeled and color-coded so you can easily design a layout that works for your site, even if you’re a beginner. </p>\n<p>If you want to add a new section to your layout, you can do so with 1 click and then insert new modules to that section with another couple clicks of a button. </p>\n<p>Divi’s Default Editor lets you see the “skeleton” of your website layout, it’s like building blocks for your website theme. But if you prefer a theme editor that’s a little more visual, don’t worry, Divi offers that too, which we’ll go over later. </p>\n<h3>Ready to Use Layouts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >The Divi Theme</a> ships with hundreds of ready to use layout packs. These are complete designs with different layouts and colors giving you a jump start in setting up your theme. All pre-made layouts are easily and infinitely customizable.</p>\n<p>Using a website pack is especially helpful if you don&#8217;t want to build a brand new design for your site from scratch. All you have to do is to select the right website pack from the library and import it to your WordPress and then make the necessary customization. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Divi-Builder-Library-of-Layouts.jpg\" alt=\"divi-layouts-library\" width=\"695\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232071\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Divi-Builder-Library-of-Layouts.jpg 695w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Divi-Builder-Library-of-Layouts-300x216.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px\" /></p>\n<p>Each website pack is designed for a specific type of website and includes 7-8 pages/layouts that are suited to that particular website type. Since these layouts are pre-built, all you need to do is import the layout and add your own content. </p>\n<p>You can browse the layouts by categories such as Fashion &#038; Beauty, Technology, Health &#038; Fitness, Services, and more. Or, simply search for the perfect layout by typing in your keywords. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-yoga-layout.jpg\" alt=\"divi-yoga-layout\" width=\"740\" height=\"419\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232072\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-yoga-layout.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-yoga-layout-300x170.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Plus, as part of the Divi Design Initiative, Divi claims they’ll be adding a new layout pack every week. </p>\n<p>With Divi Layouts, you can easily and quickly build web pages that are suited to your exact needs. </p>\n<h3>Instantly Add From 46+ Content Modules to Divi Layout</h3>\n<p>Modules are the building blocks in Divi theme, also known as elements. There are 46 content modules that you can add to any page or layout in your theme. Content modules include slider, accordion, portfolio, call to action, galleries, videos, social buttons, and so much more.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-content-modules.jpg\" alt=\"divi-content-modules\" width=\"672\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232073\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-content-modules.jpg 672w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-content-modules-300x223.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 672px) 100vw, 672px\" /></p>\n<p>You can easily add content modules to customize your theme by simply dragging a module to a page. Alternatively, you can add it from the Live Preview by clicking on the (+) button, locating the content module of your choice, and clicking it to add it to the section.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-add-module.jpg\" alt=\"divi-add-module\" width=\"740\" height=\"454\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232074\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-add-module.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-add-module-300x184.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Most content modules are customizable as well, so you’re not stuck with the default module style. You can choose the colors, text, sizing, image, borders, and more. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-customize-module.jpg\" alt=\"customize-divi-modules\" width=\"740\" height=\"385\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232075\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-customize-module.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-customize-module-300x156.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>This gives you total control over how your theme looks, so you won’t have a website that looks like anyone else’s. </p>\n<h3>Superb Divi Feature: Live Preview Customizer</h3>\n<p>With WordPress, when designing your site, you have to click on the Preview button to open a new window to see what your site looks like. But with Divi’s Live Preview, you can see exactly what your website will look like as you’re building it.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-live-editing.jpg\" alt=\"divi-live-preview\" width=\"740\" height=\"380\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232076\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-live-editing.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-live-editing-300x154.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /> </p>\n<p>The fast and easy-to-use Live Preview customizer allows you to change colors, fonts, style, and more. This makes customization easier for even the beginner users as they can see their changes right away and can undo them at any time.</p>\n<p>Since Divi gives you the option of customizing your theme with the Default Editor or Visual Builder, you can choose which works best for you. Or, use a combination of both to build your theme exactly as you want. </p>\n<h3>Divi&#8217;s Plugin Compatibility</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-usebuilder.jpg\" alt=\"divi-wordpress\" width=\"740\" height=\"370\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232077\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-usebuilder.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-usebuilder-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Want to start an eCommerce website? <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> also supports <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/woocommerce/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >WooCommerce</a>, one of the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-ecommerce-plugins-compared/\">best eCommerce plugins</a> on the market, right out of the box. </p>\n<p>With a Divi online store layout and the WooCommerce plugin, you can quickly build the online store of your dreams. Your online store will look incredible on all devices and you can still use your Divi theme to create different sections of your website. Their online store layouts also come with all of the pages you need to sell your products including a cart page and checkout page. </p>\n<p>Divi shop page layouts also come pre-built with shop modules so you can easily organize your products into categories like featured, on sale, and more.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-online-store.jpg\" alt=\"divi-online-store\" width=\"740\" height=\"420\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232081\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-online-store.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-online-store-300x170.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /> </p>\n<p>In addition, Divi comes in 32 languages with RTL support. Translations include both the backend and front-end of your website. It also supports WPML so you can create multilingual websites with the same incredible theme.</p>\n<h3>Sucuri Safe Theme</h3>\n<p>A security vulnerability in a WordPress theme or a plugin can compromise the security of your website. </p>\n<p>The code behind the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> theme is audited by <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/sucuri/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Sucuri</a>, one of the leading web security firms in the world. After careful study of the code, the Sucuri&#8217;s security experts gave Divi their safe theme seal.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-sucuri.jpg\" alt=\"divi-security\" width=\"740\" height=\"416\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232079\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-sucuri.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-sucuri-300x169.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<blockquote><p>It is the opinion of the review team that this theme was developed extremely well and as such, the Divi Theme is deserving of the Safe Theme seal. No significant issues were identified during the vulnerability assessment. No issues were identified in the code audit</p>\n<footer>&#8211; Sucuri Team</footer>\n</blockquote>\n<h2>Divi Pricing</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> offers 2 different pricing plans: Yearly Access and Lifetime Access. You can pay $89 per year, which is their most popular plan, or a 1-time price of $249 to get lifetime access and updates. Both plans give you access to all themes (Divi and Extra) and plugins (Bloom and Monarch), theme updates, premium support, unlimited website usage, and a risk-free guarantee. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/divi-pricing.png\" alt=\"divi pricing\" width=\"740\" height=\"419\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233864\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/divi-pricing.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/divi-pricing-300x170.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<h2>Divi Customer Support and Documentation</h2>\n<p>When you purchase <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> by Elegant Themes, you get complete access to the extensive documentation, support forums, and their awesome support team.</p>\n<p>Elegant Themes has a well-trained staff of professionals who are always available to help with your theme questions. </p>\n<p>In addition, Elegant Themes also runs a helpful blog that includes tutorials and guides with easy-to-follow steps and screenshots to help you learn how to do anything and everything with Divi. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-blog.jpg\" alt=\"divi-support-blog\" width=\"740\" height=\"396\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232102\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-blog.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/divi-blog-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Their support license also allows you to install Divi on as many sites as you want. You can even use it to build client sites.</p>\n<p>Technical support is only offered via ticket based emails.</p>\n<h2>Our Verdict on Using Divi Builder and Divi Theme</h2>\n<p>We carefully examined the incredible features offered in <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a>. After test driving it for a while, we found Divi to be an excellent choice for anyone who wants to build a stunning website with ease. We give it 5 out of 5 stars.</p>\n<p>If you enjoyed our Divi review, you might want to check out our review on WP Bakery Page Builder</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-themes/divi-theme-review/\">Divi Theme &#038; Builder Review (2019): Is It Worth the Price?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-themes/divi-theme-review/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:62:\"How To Start a Fashion Website with WordPress &amp; Make Money\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"https://www.isitwp.com/start-a-fashion-website/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://www.isitwp.com/start-a-fashion-website/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 30 May 2019 11:01:18 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"create a fashion website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"fashion\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"fashion website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"start a fashion website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=232309\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:601:\"<p>Do you want to build a fashion or clothing website? Starting a fashion website or blog with WordPress is easy. You can use WordPress fashion themes to give your website a glamorous look. If you follow the right steps, then you can also convert it into a profitable business. In this article, we&#8217;ll share how [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/start-a-fashion-website/\">How To Start a Fashion Website with WordPress &#038; Make Money</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13844:\"<p>Do you want to build a fashion or clothing website?</p>\n<p>Starting a fashion website or blog with WordPress is easy. You can use WordPress fashion themes to give your website a glamorous look. If you follow the right steps, then you can also convert it into a profitable business.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll share how to start a fashion website with WordPress and make money from it.</p>\n<h3>Building a Fashion Website with WordPress</h3>\n<p>There are many bloggers on Instagram and Facebook promoting the top fashion brands from their official profiles. These fashion brands settle a deal with the bloggers for promotion of their products.</p>\n<p>However, you have no control over the content that you share on social media platforms like Instagram and Facebook. If someday your account is deleted or anything goes wrong, then you may lose everything you&#8217;ve built over the years.</p>\n<p>When you build a fashion website, you have full control over your content. You can even monetize your content and make money on the side. </p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at how to start a fashion website with WordPress and make money in the right way.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Getting a Domain Name and Web Hosting</h3>\n<p>The first thing you&#8217;ll need is a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/difference-between-domain-name-and-web-hosting-revealed/\" title=\"What’s the Difference Between Domain Name and Web Hosting? (REVEALED)\">domain name and web hosting</a>.</p>\n<p>A domain name is the address of your website on the internet, like Google.com or IsItWP.com. It’s what your visitors type into their browsers to access your website. A domain name costs around $15 / month.</p>\n<p>Web hosting is where people store the content and files of their websites. When someone types in your web address (domain name), then they’ll be directed to the website files stored on your web hosting server. A web hosting account will cost around $9 / month. </p>\n<p>When you&#8217;re starting out, the combined cost of a domain name and web hosting may seem like quite a lot. </p>\n<p>Fortunately, we&#8217;ve partnered with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" title=\"Bluehost\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Bluehost</a> to offer our users a free domain name, free SSL certificate, and a huge discount on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/\" title=\"Top 10 Web Hosting Companies (Real Reviews, No B.S)\">web hosting</a>.</p>\n<p>You only have to pay $2.75 / month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Claim This Exclusive Bluehost Offer&raquo;</a></p>\n<p>After purchasing the web hosting, you can go ahead and install WordPress on your hosting account.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Installing WordPress</h3>\n<p>With Bluehost, you don&#8217;t have to go through a separate WordPress installation process because Bluehost now installs WordPress by default. After subscribing to your hosting plan, you&#8217;ll be prompted to choose a WordPress theme.<br />\nYou should log in to your web hosting cPanel account. There, you&#8217;ll see the 1-click WordPress installer which saves the trouble of manually installing WordPress.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"Install WordPress\" width=\"775\" height=\"328\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232955\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-wordpress.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-wordpress-300x127.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/install-wordpress-768x325.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>We&#8217;re using <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" title=\"Bluehost\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Bluehost</a>, so the 1-click WordPress install is available as a feature in the cPanel account. It can be slightly different if you&#8217;re using any other web hosting provider.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll need to fill all the required details and install WordPress easily. For more information, you should check out our complete and step by step guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-wordpress-complete-wordpress-installation-tutorial/\" title=\"How to Install WordPress – The Complete WordPress Installation Tutorial\">how to properly install WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pick-a-theme.png\" alt=\"pick a theme\" width=\"600\" height=\"276\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218387\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pick-a-theme.png 600w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pick-a-theme-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll then be asked to choose the name and tagline for your website. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog.jpg\" alt=\"create a new wordpress website\" width=\"775\" height=\"472\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218383\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog-300x183.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog-768x468.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After specifying the details, click <strong>Next</strong>. Bluehost will now install WordPress for you and, once done, will show you a screen like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress installation successful\" width=\"775\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218385\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful-300x185.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful-768x474.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can login to your site by appending <strong>wp-admin</strong> to your URL. Here&#8217;s what your WordPress login URL should look like: </p>\n<p>http://example.com/wp-admin</p>\n<p>You can now login to your WordPress website with the credentials sent to your email address. </p>\n<h3>Step 3: Selecting a Theme for Your Fashion Website</h3>\n<p>Once you installed WordPress, you&#8217;ll need to choose a theme that matches your requirements for a fashion website.</p>\n<p>There are hundreds of free and premium WordPress themes on the internet. Let&#8217;s choose any theme that you see now. You can always change the theme after your WordPress setup. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-themes.jpg\" alt=\"Fashion themes\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232959\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-themes.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-themes-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-themes-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>A good fashion theme allows you to add your photos, portfolio, and content beautifully. It should have different page templates for your blog and <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-landing-page-plugins/\" title=\"7 Best WordPress Landing Page Plugins That Convert\">landing pages</a>.</p>\n<p>For more details, you should check out this guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-install-a-wordpress-theme/\" title=\"How to install a WordPress theme\">how to install a WordPress theme</a>.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Publishing Fashion Photos and Content</h3>\n<p>Before you make your website public, you should add photos and content to it.</p>\n<p>Usually, it takes time to have enough content. You can also integrate your Instagram account and share photos directly from Instagram with your website audience.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-photos-ig.jpg\" alt=\"Fashion photos\" width=\"1117\" height=\"540\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232968\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-photos-ig.jpg 1117w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-photos-ig-300x145.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-photos-ig-768x371.jpg 768w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-photos-ig-1024x495.jpg 1024w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-photos-ig-330x160.jpg 330w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1117px) 100vw, 1117px\" /></p>\n<p>Furthermore, you&#8217;ll need to make the website pages like about, services, and <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\" title=\"7 Best WordPress Contact Form Plugins Compared\">contact form</a> page. We recommend using a page builder plugin like <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/beaver-builder/\" title=\"Beaver Builder\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Beaver Builder</a> or <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/elementor-pro/\" title=\"Elementor\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Elementor</a>. These <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-page-builders-compared/\" title=\"7 Best Drag and Drop WordPress Page Builders Compared\">drag and drop page builders</a> will help you set up the landing pages and add content instantly.</p>\n<p>You should also <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-start-a-blog-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Start a WordPress Blog (&#038; Make Extra Income)\">start a blog</a> and create a content strategy to post articles regularly. Look into the top fashion blogs and vlogs for inspiration.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-blog.jpg\" alt=\"Top fashion blog\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232966\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-blog.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-blog-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/fashion-blog-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can create professional image galleries on the homepage and landing pages. With WordPress, you&#8217;ll find the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-gallery-plugins-compared/\" title=\"8 Best WordPress Gallery Plugins Compared\">best image gallery plugins</a> that has features like image styling, lightbox popup, etc.</p>\n<h3>Step 5: Making Your Fashion Website SEO Friendly</h3>\n<p>Once your website is ready, you&#8217;ll need to make sure that it&#8217;s available to everyone looking for fashion related products and content. You need to optimize your site and make it search engine friendly. This way, your fashion website will start appearing in the Google search results.</p>\n<p>WordPress websites are <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/seo-friendly/\" title=\"How to Make Your WordPress Site SEO Friendly\">SEO friendly</a> by default, but you can still take a few steps to ensure that your site is visible to everyone looking for fashion related content.</p>\n<p>The best practices of SEO include speed and performance optimization. When your users visit the website, and it loads quickly, it leaves an excellent first impression which lasts long. You can use WordPress caching plugins like <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wp-rocket/\" title=\"WP Rocket\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">WP Rocket</a> to speed up your website.</p>\n<p>Next, you need to track user engagement on your website so you can make an informed decision on what works best for your audience. Tracking will help you understand user behavior and where the users&#8217; are losing interest. For this, you need to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-google-analytics-wordpress-site/\" title=\"How to Install Google Analytics on Your WordPress Site\">install Google analytics on your fashion website</a>.</p>\n<p>The analytics will show you all the details about pages visited and the action taken by your users. If most of your website visitors are leaving from a specific page, it means you need to address the issue and make that page more engaging for users.</p>\n<h3>Step 6: Make Money from Your Fashion Website</h3>\n<p>There are multiple ways to make money from your fashion website. Let&#8217;s take a look at a few of them below. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Google AdSense: AdSense is a Google-owned advertising network that allows bloggers and website owners to monetize their fashion website by displaying text, image, video, and other interactive advertisements on their websites.</li>\n<li>Affiliate marketing: Top fashion brands and clothing stores run affiliate programs, which means you can promote their products to earn a good commission whenever you make a sale. </li>\n<li>Sell direct ads: The benefit of selling direct ads is that you don&#8217;t have to share ad revenue with a third-party ad network like Google AdSense. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>For more details, you can check out <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/legit-ways-to-make-money-online-blogging/\">30 ways to make money online</a>.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it.</p>\n<p>We hope this guide has helped you learn how to start a fashion website with WordPress. You may also want to check out our article on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-photography-themes-for-wordpress/\" title=\"43 Best Photography Themes for WordPress\">best photography themes for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/start-a-fashion-website/\">How To Start a Fashion Website with WordPress &#038; Make Money</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:52:\"https://www.isitwp.com/start-a-fashion-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"Divi vs. Avada: Which Theme is BEST for You? (Compared)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:37:\"https://www.isitwp.com/divi-vs-avada/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://www.isitwp.com/divi-vs-avada/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 29 May 2019 10:40:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Resources\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"avada\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"divi\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"divi vs avada\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"wordpress theme\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=231280\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:594:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress theme for your website? If you&#8217;re reading this, you&#8217;ve likely already done the bulk of the work. You&#8217;ve narrowed your search down to 2 choices: Divi or Avada. But which one is truly the best? Outwardly, these 2 popular themes may seem similar in terms of features and [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/divi-vs-avada/\">Divi vs. Avada: Which Theme is BEST for You? (Compared)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15560:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress theme for your website? If you&#8217;re reading this, you&#8217;ve likely already done the bulk of the work. You&#8217;ve narrowed your search down to 2 choices: Divi or Avada. But which one is truly the best?</p>\n<p>Outwardly, these 2 popular themes may seem similar in terms of features and flexibility. Which is why, for this in-depth comparison, we&#8217;ll be digging deep! We&#8217;ll inspect each theme&#8217;s ease of use, features, available documentation, and pricing to determine which theme wins the battle: Divi vs. Avada.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s rock!</p>\n<h3>Overview: Divi vs. Avada</h3>\n<p><strong>Divi</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-1.jpg\" alt=\"Divi\" width=\"775\" height=\"340\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-231740\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-1.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-1-300x132.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-1-768x337.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/elegant-themes-divi/\" title=\"Divi\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Divi</a> is a super flexible, powerful WordPress theme. It was built by Elegant Themes, an extremely popular WordPress themes marketplace. You can use it as a parent theme to numerous WordPress themes including all themes built by Elegant Themes. Divi is sold bundled with Elegant Themes&#8217; club membership.</p>\n<p>This theme is well-known for the advanced drag and drop Divi Builder, which works great with many popular WordPress themes. The Divi Builder helps you create pages instantly, without writing a single line of code. You can simply move the elements on the builder using your mouse to design your pages.</p>\n<p>Divi is easy-to-use and enormously popular with beginners who&#8217;re looking to set up a blog or website.</p>\n<p><strong>Avada</strong></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada.jpg\" alt=\"Avada\" width=\"775\" height=\"340\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-231739\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-300x132.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-768x337.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" title=\"Avada\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Avada</a> has been a best-selling WordPress theme consistently for several years at this point. It can be used to create any type of website, blog, landing page, or online store. It ships with tons of useful WordPress plugins that you can use to make your website stand out from the crowd.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to set up within WordPress. You can use popular page builder plugins to design pages with Avada. It also comes with multiple pre-built designs you can customize, so you can have the website you desire without having to design it completely from scratch. It&#8217;s packed with unlimited colors and styles.</p>\n<p>Avada is trusted by thousands of users and it&#8217;s the most sold theme from many marketplaces.</p>\n<h3>Features: Divi vs. Avada</h3>\n<p><strong>Divi</strong></p>\n<p>As one of the most popular WordPress themes in existence, it&#8217;s no surprise <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/elegant-themes-divi/\" title=\"Divi\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Divi</a> has tons of amazing features. It all starts with their exclusive Divi Builder, a powerful drag and drop builder for moving elements on your theme page. The Divi Builder makes it simple for you to design your own pages. You can draw columns and rows to add modules to via drag and drop.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-builder.jpg\" alt=\"Divi builder\" width=\"775\" height=\"306\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-231823\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-builder.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-builder-300x118.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-builder-768x303.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Other notable features include the multiple ready-made <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-divi-layouts/\" title=\"11 Best Divi Layouts and Supported Themes for Divi Builder\">Divi layouts</a> and designs bundled with Divi theme. These layouts instantly give your website a professional look. Divi theme has a layout for nearly every kind of website imaginable. You can simply select a layout and make a few tweaks to personalize it for your brand. These pre-built layouts will save you vast amounts of time because you won&#8217;t have to manually edit the theme from scratch.</p>\n<p>Also, check out these highly customizable <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-divi-child-themes/\" title=\"7 Best Divi Child Themes for a Highly Customized Website\">Divi child themes</a>.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the Divi theme has multiple content types and modules. These content modules allow you to insert different types of content and media on your website. You can use the Divi Builder to adjust these modules within any section. With the live WordPress customizer, you can also preview the final results before publishing.</p>\n<p>Divi theme has powerful, practical integrations. It works perfectly with WooCommerce to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-create-an-online-store-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Create an Online Store – Step by Step (with Pictures)\">create an online store</a>. Like other modules on the theme, you can use the Divi Builder to design your eCommerce shop. Divi supports WPML and multiple RTL languages to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/easily-create-multilingual-wordpress-website/\" title=\"How to Easily Create a Multilingual WordPress Website (Step by Step)\">create a multilingual website</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Avada</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" title=\"Avada\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Avada</a> has a wide range of useful features. It&#8217;s truly a multipurpose WordPress theme and can be used to create any kind of website. They included unlimited designs and templates help you build a website catered to your specific business niche in no time flat. All these designs are fully customizable so you can quickly change colors and styles. You can edit the templates using the simple theme options panel.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-layouts.jpg\" alt=\"Avada designs and layouts\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-231822\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-layouts.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-layouts-300x135.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-layouts-768x347.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>It ships with a Fusion Core plugin designed specifically for the Avada theme. The plugin adds the Fusion page builder for easier customization. You can use the page builder to create your landing pages with all other features of the Avada theme. In addition to the page builder, you&#8217;ll also get an image slider, mega menu, and a shortcode generator.</p>\n<p>When it comes to integrations, Avada theme can be flawlessly combined with the WooCommerce WordPress plugin to turn your website into an eCommerce store. You can align other features of the Avada theme with your online store to make it eye-catching and stylish. Avada also supports bbPress forums to launch a forum within your website. Other integrations include Font Awesome icons to add beautiful icons to your navigation menus, social media menus, etc.</p>\n<p>Avada comes packed with several WordPress plugins, including Revolution Slider, Layer Slider, Elastic Slider, and more. The theme is highly responsive, and it works great on all screen sizes and devices.</p>\n<h3>Ease of Use: Divi vs. Avada</h3>\n<p><strong>Divi</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/elegant-themes-divi/\" title=\"Divi\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Divi</a> is easy to set up and beginner-friendly from the installation process to ultimately launching your site. It has professional designs and layouts to use as a jumping off point. You just need to add in your own content and your website will be ready to roll.</p>\n<p>The features of the Divi theme make it really easy even for absolute beginners to design a professional-looking website. With simple customization options, you can add or remove any module from your site. It has an easy-to-understand control panel to manage your website&#8217;s features.</p>\n<p><strong>Avada</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" title=\"Avada\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Avada</a> has so many features that many assume you need professional development skills to use the theme. However, it&#8217;s designed in such a way that even a user with little-to-no coding knowledge can install Avada and reap its benefits.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-features.jpg\" alt=\"Avada features\" width=\"775\" height=\"288\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-231824\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-features.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-features-300x111.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/avada-features-768x285.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>To make it look like the demo websites, you&#8217;ll need to add your content within the theme. Avada is flexible for creating landing pages, image sliders, portfolios, slideshows, etc. The Fusion page builder gives you full control of your site&#8217;s design and layout. It also allows you to create your own website design using its simple drag and drop functionality.</p>\n<p>Avada has a demo installer which helps greatly when you&#8217;re getting started. It&#8217;ll display a website similar to the chosen demo and you can quickly replace the dummy content to add your own.</p>\n<h3>Support and Documentation: Divi vs. Avada</h3>\n<p><strong>Divi</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/elegant-themes-divi/\" title=\"Divi\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Divi</a> theme comes with Elegant Themes&#8217; club membership which, in turn, gives you complete access to their extensive documentation, support forums, and their customer support team.</p>\n<p>Elegant Themes has a well-trained staff of professionals who&#8217;re available to help with your theme questions. Your membership gives you support access for a year, after which you can renew your subscription if you need additional support.</p>\n<p>This support license also allows you to install Divi on as many sites as you want. You can even use it to build client sites. Your license also entitles you to free theme updates.</p>\n<p><strong>Avada</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" title=\"Avada\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Avada</a> theme boasts about its support team on their website, and with good reason. Their team provides real support from the actual people who created the theme.</p>\n<p>Avada is very well-documented. Every feature of the theme is explained in detail and has step-by-step instructions included in the theme&#8217;s documentation. Documentation is also available for the additional plugins that are shipped with Avada.</p>\n<h3>Pricing: Divi vs. Avada</h3>\n<p><strong>Divi</strong></p>\n<p>To get the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/elegant-themes-divi/\" title=\"Divi\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Divi theme</a>, you&#8217;ll need to sign up for an Elegant Themes membership. It has 2 plans: Yearly Access and Lifetime Access.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-pricing.jpg\" alt=\"Divi pricing\" width=\"775\" height=\"450\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-231821\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-pricing.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-pricing-300x174.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/divi-pricing-768x446.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>The yearly access plan includes all the themes and plugins available from Elegant Themes, including Divi. It has unlimited website usage and a yearly renewal for $89 / year. This plan includes theme updates and premium customer support from the professional team behind Elegant Themes.</p>\n<p>However, the lifetime access plan costs $249. It offers everything included in the yearly access plan for a one-time fee. Once paid, you&#8217;ll have access to the themes and plugins from Elegant Themes for the lifetime of the company. This plan also includes lifetime theme updates and professional customer support.</p>\n<p>You have the flexibility to cancel your membership or upgrade/downgrade to any plan at any time. </p>\n<p><strong>Avada</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" title=\"Avada\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Avada</a> theme has a regular license that costs $60 / year. It includes 6 months of customer support, theme updates, and all of Avada&#8217;s features. You can extend the customer support to 1 year by paying an additional $18 with the regular license.</p>\n<p>The pricing is very reasonable when compared to other WordPress themes with features similar to Avada&#8217;s.</p>\n<h3>Our Verdict: Divi vs. Avada &#8211; Which Theme Should You Choose?</h3>\n<p>Without a doubt, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/divi/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Divi</a> is one of the most popular WordPress themes on the market. With its drag and drop builder, you can build a website the way you want. Whether you&#8217;re an absolute newbie or a seasoned developer, Divi will be the best choice for your needs. </p>\n<p>A newbie can easily create a website without hiring a professional. A developer can easily build hundreds of websites for their clients&#8217; thanks to full website packs. Check out this <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-themes/divi-theme-review/\" title=\"Divi Theme &#038; Builder Review: Is It Worth the Price?\">Divi theme review</a>.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re after an all-in-one theme that&#8217;s shipped with tons of useful plugins and built-in features, then you might consider buying <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/avada/\" title=\"Avada\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Avada</a>. The main benefit is that you aren&#8217;t limited to a single site; you can use Avada to create as many websites as you want. Avada has all the features you&#8217;d expect from what&#8217;s considered the world&#8217;s most powerful and trusted WordPress theme.</p>\n<p>We hope you enjoyed this article comparing Divi vs. Avada and that you now have a better idea of which is the best theme for your website. If you liked this article, you might also like our post on the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-free-wordpress-blog-themes/\" title=\"62 Best Free WordPress Blog Themes\">best FREE WordPress blog themes</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/divi-vs-avada/\">Divi vs. Avada: Which Theme is BEST for You? (Compared)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"https://www.isitwp.com/divi-vs-avada/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"5\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"How to Build an Online Marketplace in WordPress (2019)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://www.isitwp.com/build-an-online-marketplace/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://www.isitwp.com/build-an-online-marketplace/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 28 May 2019 10:29:13 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"build an online marketplace\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"marketplace\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"online marketplace\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"online marketplace wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"wordpress marketplace\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=232178\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:607:\"<p>Do you want to build an online marketplace in WordPress? Building an online marketplace is one of the best ways to make money online. While it’s not a get-rich-quick scheme, with the right strategies, it’s totally possible to earn a solid income with an online marketplace. In this article, we’ll show you how to build [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/build-an-online-marketplace/\">How to Build an Online Marketplace in WordPress (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17713:\"<p>Do you want to build an online marketplace in WordPress?</p>\n<p>Building an online marketplace is one of the best ways to make money online. While it’s not a get-rich-quick scheme, with the right strategies, it’s totally possible to earn a solid income with an online marketplace.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to build an online marketplace in WordPress.</p>\n<h3>What Is an Online Marketplace?</h3>\n<p>An online marketplace is a type of eCommerce website that allows users to become a seller and list their products for sale.  As a marketplace owner, you don’t own any inventory. Your business is to allow users to list their products on your website and facilitate the transaction.</p>\n<p>You can make money by earning a specific commission for each sale on your marketplace.</p>\n<p>eBay is the perfect example of an online marketplace.</p>\n<h3>How Much Does it Cost to Make an Online Marketplace?</h3>\n<p>A physical marketplace would cost millions of dollars and consumes years to set up. However, an online marketplace can be built in less than an hour and costs as low as $6.95 / month.</p>\n<p>Here are the tools you’ll need to build an online marketplace and let&#8217;s see how much they cost:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Domain name </strong>($14.95 / year): A domain name is the address of your website on the internet, like Google.com or IsItWP.com. It’s what your visitors type into their browsers to access your website.</li>\n<li><strong>Web hosting </strong>($13.99 / month): Web hosting is where people store the content and files of their websites. When someone types in your web address (domain name), then they’ll be directed to the website files stored on your web hosting server.</li>\n<li><strong>WordPress </strong>(free): WordPress is the most reliable and popular platform for building any kind of website, including a marketplace.</li>\n<li><strong>WooCommerce </strong>(free): WooCommerce is the world’s largest eCommerce plugin for WordPress.</li>\n<li><strong>WC Wendors plugin </strong>(free): This is the #1 marketplace plugin for WooCommerce that transforms an eCommerce website into a fully-fledging marketplace.</li>\n<li><strong>SSL certificate </strong>($6.67/month): SSL adds a green padlock icon to the address bar, telling your customers that your website is trustworthy to process an online transaction.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>That means the combined cost of building a website will cost around $263 annually, meaning $22 / month. When you’re starting out, this seems like a bit expensive. That’s why we’ve negotiated a deal with Bluehost to offer our users everything they need for $6.95 / month. Pay annually and <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/bluehost-offer-monthly-payment/\" title=\"Does Bluehost Offer Monthly Payment? (Must-Know Facts!)\">save more on Bluehost</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost-woocommerce/\" title=\"Bluehost\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-woocommerce-refer.jpg\" alt=\"bluehost-woocommerce-refer\" width=\"740\" height=\"361\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232807\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-woocommerce-refer.jpg 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-woocommerce-refer-300x146.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/bluehost-woocommerce-refer-330x160.jpg 330w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost-woocommerce/\" title=\"Bluehost\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Bluehost</a> is an officially recommended WordPress hosting provider by WordPress.org. They offer a wide variety of hosting options, but for an online marketplace, we recommend their WooCommerce hosting, which comes bundled with everything you need for a marketplace.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost-woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Claim This Exclusive Bluehost Offer&raquo;</a></p>\n<h3>Step 1: Creating an Online Store with WordPress</h3>\n<p>First, you&#8217;ll need to follow our step by step guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-create-an-online-store-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Create an Online Store – Step by Step (with Pictures)\">create an online store</a> in WordPress using WooCommerce.</p>\n<p>Though WooCommerce is a powerful plugin, it creates a single vendor store and only you can add products. This store doesn&#8217;t allow vendors to sign up which means you&#8217;ll need an addon or plugin to convert your online store into a marketplace.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Switching Your Store into a Marketplace Using a Plugin</h3>\n<p>Once your online store is ready, you can go ahead and install the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wc-vendors/\" title=\"WC Vendors\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">WC Vendors</a> plugin. For more details, you should check out our article on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-wordpress-plugin/\" title=\"How to Install a WordPress Plugin\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>WC Vendors plugin will work as an addon to turn your single vendor online store into a multi-vendor marketplace. Once you set it up, the vendors can sign up, add their products, and sell online from your website.</p>\n<p>As an administrator, you can control the vendors and marketplace. The plugin allows you to set a commission percentage on sales, product categories, payment gateways, and more.</p>\n<p>Once activated, you can go ahead to <strong>WC Vendors &raquo; Settings</strong> page to make changes on your website.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wcvendor-settings.jpg\" alt=\"WC Vendors settings\" width=\"775\" height=\"390\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232182\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wcvendor-settings.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wcvendor-settings-300x151.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wcvendor-settings-768x386.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>In the general settings, you&#8217;ll find the following options:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Allow vendor registrations</li>\n<li>Terms &#038; conditions checkbox</li>\n<li>Manual vendor approval</li>\n<li>Become a vendor link</li>\n</ul>\n<p>There are other settings as well. You can select the options that you want to enable on your marketplace.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Click on the &#8216;Save Changes&#8217; button before you move to other tabs for further settings.</p>\n<p>After that, you can switch to &#8216;Commission&#8217; tab to add the commission settings for the vendors. The percentage you add in this field will be the amount paid to vendors for their sales.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/commision.jpg\" alt=\"Commision\" width=\"775\" height=\"215\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232183\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/commision.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/commision-300x83.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/commision-768x213.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also add a separate commission percentage for each vendor and products.</p>\n<p>Now you can go to &#8216;Capabilities&#8217; tab to manage the vendors&#8217; permissions. The general capabilities settings have multiple options that include allowing vendors to add/edit products, push products directly to the marketplace without approval, view and export orders, and front end sales reports.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/capabilities.jpg\" alt=\"Capabilities\" width=\"775\" height=\"435\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232185\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/capabilities.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/capabilities-300x168.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/capabilities-768x431.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>If you switch to &#8216;Products&#8217; settings under the Capabilities tab, you can add product types, type options, product data tabs, and allow vendors to add featured products.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/product-capabilities.jpg\" alt=\"Product capabilities\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232186\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/product-capabilities.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/product-capabilities-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/product-capabilities-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you can go to &#8216;Orders&#8217; settings to configure what a vendor should see for an order they receive. There are multiple settings that include allowing vendors to see order notes, add order notes, see customers name, shipping name, addresses, and more.</p>\n<p>You can simply uncheck any setting that you don&#8217;t want the vendors to see for their orders.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/orders-capabilities.jpg\" alt=\"Orders capabilities\" width=\"775\" height=\"430\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232188\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/orders-capabilities.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/orders-capabilities-300x166.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/orders-capabilities-768x426.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done with the vendors&#8217; capabilities settings, you can head over to &#8216;Display&#8217; tab.</p>\n<p>It has custom settings to create pages for vendors. To create pages, you can go to <strong>Pages &raquo; Add New</strong> in WordPress and add the shortcodes given under each dropdown.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/display-page-shortcodes.jpg\" alt=\"Display page shortcodes\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232189\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/display-page-shortcodes.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/display-page-shortcodes-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/display-page-shortcodes-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After creating pages with these shortcodes, simply return to choose those pages under the &#8216;Display&#8217; tab.</p>\n<p>Scroll down on the same page to &#8216;Store Settings&#8217; and change the individual vendor&#8217;s store options that include vendor store URL, display shop header template, display shop name, etc.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/storesettings.jpg\" alt=\"Store settings\" width=\"775\" height=\"385\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232190\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/storesettings.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/storesettings-300x149.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/storesettings-768x382.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you can go to the &#8216;Payments&#8217; tab. If you have experience with the online marketplaces, you would know that the vendors get paid on weekly, bi-weekly, and monthly net.</p>\n<p>However, the recommended way is to clear the payments manually. In the meantime, you can monitor the product reviews and process the customers&#8217; refund requests.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payments.jpg\" alt=\"Payments\" width=\"775\" height=\"195\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232191\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payments.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payments-300x75.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payments-768x193.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also use the <a href=\"https://www.wcvendors.com/2018/05/payments-explained/\" title=\"Paid addons\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">paid addons</a> from WC Vendors to set up automatic payments to vendors. This plugin supports Stripe, Escrow, MangoPay, and more.</p>\n<p>Each payment method has its own settings. Once you select a payment gateway, you may need to enter your API keys for the payments to process smoothly.</p>\n<p>This completes the settings for WC Vendors plugin. Head back to WooCommerce settings to enable account management for customers.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Allowing Customers to Create an Account</h3>\n<p>Simply go to <strong>WooCommerce &raquo; Settings</strong> page. Under the &#8216;Accounts and Privacy&#8217; tab, you need to select all settings for account creation.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/account-creation.jpg\" alt=\"Account creation\" width=\"775\" height=\"295\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232193\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/account-creation.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/account-creation-300x114.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/account-creation-768x292.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Scroll to the bottom and click on the &#8216;Save Changes&#8217; button.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Adding Accounts Page to Your Navigation Menu</h3>\n<p>Next, you can go ahead and put the account registration option on your navigation menu. It will ease the customer registration process and all your users can sign up quickly.</p>\n<p>You need to visit <strong>Appearance &raquo; Menus</strong> page to add My Account and Checkout pages to your navigation menu.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/menu-settings.jpg\" alt=\"Menu settings\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232194\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/menu-settings.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/menu-settings-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/menu-settings-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After adding these pages, click on the &#8216;Save Menu&#8217; button to continue.</p>\n<p>If there&#8217;s no &#8216;My Account&#8217; page available, then go ahead and create a new page with &#8216;My Account&#8217; as the title. You need to add this shortcode on the page:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n[woocommerce_my_account]\r\n</pre>\n<h3>Step 5: Run and Manage Your Online Marketplace</h3>\n<p>Once your online marketplace is ready, you can test if everything works as expected by creating a new account, approving test pending vendor requests, and more.</p>\n<p>The vendors can register for an account and log into their accounts from your website.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/vendor-registration.jpg\" alt=\"Vendors registration\" width=\"775\" height=\"363\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232200\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/vendor-registration.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/vendor-registration-300x141.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/vendor-registration-768x360.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After logging in, vendors can add their products to the online marketplace. They need to set up their shops to view orders, sales reports, and other details.</p>\n<p>All vendors should also provide payment information for getting paid, based on the payment gateway they select. For manual payment processing, vendors need to submit their bank account details.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-details.jpg\" alt=\"Payment details\" width=\"775\" height=\"332\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232201\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-details.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-details-300x129.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/payment-details-768x329.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll also get multiple email notifications on the actions taken by vendors. It includes notifications for product requests. You can approve, edit, or delete a product as you have the full control on your online marketplace.</p>\n<p>We also recommend you to check out these articles to improve your eCommerce marketplace&#8217;s performance:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/google-analytics-ecommerce-tracking-woocommerce/\" title=\"How to Set Up Google Analytics eCommerce Tracking for WooCommerce\">How to set up Google Analytics eCommerce tracking for WooCommerce</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-woocommerce-themes-online-store/\" title=\"50+ Best WooCommerce Themes for Your Online Store\">Best WooCommerce themes for your online marketplace</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>That&#8217;s all.</p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you learn how to build an online marketplace in WordPress. You may also want to check out our article on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/ecommerce/\" title=\"Best eCommerce Hosting Companies (Real Reviews)\">best eCommerce hosting companies</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/build-an-online-marketplace/\">How to Build an Online Marketplace in WordPress (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://www.isitwp.com/build-an-online-marketplace/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"7 Best Divi Child Themes for a Highly Customized Website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-divi-child-themes/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-divi-child-themes/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 27 May 2019 10:58:56 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"